1.Given an integer num, repeatedly add all its digits until the result has only one digit, and return it.

Example 1:

Input: num = 38
Output: 2
Explanation: The process is
38 --> 3 + 8 --> 11
11 --> 1 + 1 --> 2 
Since 2 has only one digit, return it.
Example 2:

Input: num = 0
Output: 0
=================================================================================================================================

class Solution:
    def addDigits(self, num: int) -> int:
        
        #num=0 return 0
        if(num==0):
            return 0
        elif (num%9) == 0:
            return 9
        return num%9



+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

TOPIC : mod 9 and why it works for ‚Äúsum of digits‚Äù

  1Ô∏è‚É£ Imagine a number as candies
        Take a number, for example: 38
        3 tens ‚Üí 30 candies
        8 ones ‚Üí 8 candies
        So total = 30 + 8 = 38 candies üç¨
2Ô∏è‚É£ Groups of 9 are special
    Why 9? Because if you put candies in groups of 9, only the leftovers matter for the sum of digits trick.
    Example:
            38 candies √∑ 9 = 4 full boxes (36 candies)
            Leftover = 2 candies ‚úÖ
            1Ô∏è‚É£ Think of numbers as blocks of 10
          
          Numbers are written in base 10: each digit is a place (ones, tens, hundreds‚Ä¶).
          Example: 38 ‚Üí 3 tens + 8 ones ‚Üí 3√ó10 + 8
          So every number = (tens √ó 10) + ones
          2Ô∏è‚É£ What happens when we group by 9
            Let‚Äôs see what happens if we divide 10 by 9:
            10 √∑ 9 = 1 full group, leftover 1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
That means 10 is like 1 plus some full 9s.

So 3 tens ‚Üí 3√ó10 = 30 ‚Üí 30 ‚â° 3 (mod 9) ‚úÖ

Add the ones ‚Üí 3 + 8 = 11 ‚Üí 1+1 = 2 ‚úÖ

Perfect! The leftover after dividing by 9 is the same as the sum of digits.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3Ô∏è‚É£ What if we try 8 instead of 9?

Divide 10 by 8:
10 √∑ 8 = 1 full group, leftover 2
Step 0: What we are doing

We want to see what happens if we try modulo 8 instead of 9.

Number = 38 = 3 tens + 8 ones = 3√ó10 + 8
------------------------------------------------------------------
We will check remainder when divided by 8.

Step 1: Find what 10 ‚â° modulo 8

10 √∑ 8 = 1 full group of 8, remainder 2

So 10 ‚â° 2 (mod 8) ‚úÖ

This means: every 10 is like 2 when working modulo 8.
-----------------------------------------------------------------

| Step | Action                                | Mod 9 Calculation                     | Result    | Mod 8 Calculation                     | Result          |
| ---- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------- | --------------- |
| 1    | Tens digit √ó 10                       | 3 √ó 10 ‚â° 3 √ó 1 (because 10 ‚â° 1 mod 9) | 3         | 3 √ó 10 ‚â° 3 √ó 2 (because 10 ‚â° 2 mod 8) | 6               |
| 2    | Add ones digit                        | 3 + 8 = 11                            | 11        | 6 + 8 = 14                            | 14              |
| 3    | Reduce modulo                         | 11 % 9 = 2                            | 2         | 14 % 8 = 6                            | 6               |
| 4    | Compare with sum of digits repeatedly | 3 + 8 = 11 ‚Üí 1 + 1 = 2 ‚úÖ              | ‚úÖ Matches | 3 + 8 = 11 ‚Üí 1 + 1 = 2 ‚ùå              | ‚ùå Doesn‚Äôt match |





